On Nov 25,  7:02pm, Bart Schaefer wrote:
} Subject: PATCH: 3.1.6-pws-9: Line numbers wrong on "unmatched" errors
}
} The ideal thing here would be to print the error message *AFTER* the
} hungetc(c); at the "brk:" label, but that requires too much rewriting.

Immediately after I sent that, I thought of the obvious way to do it.
This goes on top of the previous patch, though only to back it out.

Index: Src/lex.c
